[[File:Hamamatsu matsuri.jpg|thumb|Hamamatsu Matsuri]]
[[File:Hamamatsu festival c.JPG|thumb|right|Yatai]]
'''Hamamatsu Kite Festival''' (浜松まつり) is Japanese festival in [[Hamamatsu]]. It is generally known to have multiple kites, along with a lot of kite battles through the days it is held. The festival also displays examples of Japanese culture through food, and general items available for purchase in merchant booths at the festival.

== Detail ==
*Tako ([[Kite]] battle)
*Yatai<!--not [[Yatai (retail)]]-->
*Neri
Participants say "Oisho, oisho!"

In Hamamatsu, the first son's birth celebration is Hatsuiwai(初祝い).<ref>[http://hirosawa.info/archives/download/2592/]</ref>

{{-}}

=== Tako ===
[[File:浜松まつり.jpg|thumb|120px|Tako of Tamachi - Tagumi (田町 - た組)]]
In Hamamatsu Kite Festival, the kite battle is called Takogassen(凧合戦) and is done at Takoba(凧場).

Takoba is at [[Nakatajima]] since 1967.<ref>[http://takoken.hamazo.tv/e6001276.html]</ref>

174 kites are there.<ref>[http://chuplus.jp/hamamatsuri/index.php Chunichi Newspaper]</ref>

The kite of the first son's birth celebration is called Hatsudako(初凧).<ref>[https://www2.nhk.or.jp/archives/michi/cgi/detail.cgi?dasID=D0004990854_00000 NHK]</ref>

{{-}}

=== Yatai ===
[[File:浜松まつり御殿屋台.JPG|thumb|120px|Yatai of Matsushiro-cho - Magumi (松城町 - マ組<ref>[https://ja-jp.facebook.com/MaZusongChengDingZhengYangHui/ 松城町凧揚会（マ組）]</ref>)]]
Yatai is also called Goden-Yatai(御殿屋台).<ref>[http://hamamatsu-daisuki.net/matsuri/introduction/stall.html]</ref>

{{-}}

=== Neri ===
[[File:Japonsko_-_Hamamacu,_z_bitvy_draků_-_Tako_macuri_(1981).jpg|thumb|120px|Neri of Higashiiba-cho - Igumi (東伊場町 - い組)]]
At the house where the eldest son is born, their family offers cooking to everyone in order to appreciate their kite flying. This is called Hatsuneri(初練り).<ref>[https://www.hamamatsu-pippi.net/shiritai/ichioshi/mimiyori/docs/2015010500462/]</ref>

In Takoba, they also do Neri in order to celebrate.

